Class CsvToPropertyReader

java.lang.Object
com.example.CsvToPropertyReader
public class CsvToPropertyReader extends Object
The CsvToPropertyReader class is responsible for: - Reading property data from a CSV file. - Converting the data into a list of Property objects. - Providing filtering methods to retrieve utility functionality. This class uses Apache Commons CSV for parsing.

    • readPropertiesFromCsv

      public static List<Property> readPropertiesFromCsv()
      Reads the selected CSV file and converts its records into a list of Property objects. Ensures that required headers are present and logs any errors during parsing.
      Returns:
      A list of Property objects representing the data in the CSV file.

    • Exercise_1

      public static List<Property> Exercise_1()
      Reads properties from a CSV file and returns them as a list of Property objects. Logs the properties for verification and debugging.
      Returns:
      A list of Property objects read from the CSV file.

    • filterPropertiesByFreguesia

      public static List<Property> filterPropertiesByFreguesia(List<Property> properties, String freguesia)
      Filters properties by a specific "Freguesia".
      Parameters:
      properties - The list of Property objects to filter.
      freguesia - The name of the "Freguesia" to filter by.
      Returns:
      A list of properties that belong to the specified "Freguesia".
      Throws:
      IllegalArgumentException - If no properties are found for the specified "Freguesia".
